Customer Feedback:
{quote}
the project for the newly cloned plan is by default just the first one in the alphabetical list of project plans. Normally when cloning a plan you are cloning within the same project though
After selecting a plan to clone, the project field should auto-select the project of the plan you are cloning so that the normal case easier and quicker.
{quote}

This is similar to how JIRA will auto select the project based on issues you're viewing when creating a new issue.

The most common case is the following where double quotes would be removed by the Bamboo parser. For this case, single quotes need to be used when passing values in a Task Goal/Target/Argument field:
{code}
-Dtest.prop='test test123' deploy
{code}
